{"title":"Meriwether Cycles Ponderosa Queue is Open","link":"https://theradavist.com/meriwether-cycles-ponderosa-queue-is-open/","date":1730492738000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/09/Meriwether-Cycles-Ponderosa-Adventure-Gravel-Bike-Review-36.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/09/Meriwether-Cycles-Ponderosa-Adventure-Gravel-Bike-Review-36.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/09/Meriwether-Cycles-Ponderosa-Adventure-Gravel-Bike-Review-36.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/09/Meriwether-Cycles-Ponderosa-Adventure-Gravel-Bike-Review-36.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/meriwether-cycles/\" target=\"_blank\">Meriwether Cycle</a>‘s Ponderosa adventure gravel bike now has an open queue. The steel frame and fork will run you $2600, while the steel frame with a Wilde carbon fork is $2500. Roll on over to <a href=\"https://meriwethercycles.com/ponderosa/\" target=\"_blank\">Meriwether Cycles</a> for ordering and check out <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/meriwether-ponderosa-gravel-bike-review/\" target=\"_blank\">John’s in-depth review</a> for more on this capable gravel machine.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/meriwether-cycles-ponderosa-queue-is-open/\">Meriwether Cycles Ponderosa Queue is Open</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"deae7748dbeb381973ad2bc3ebfea97062381f7315c415b09225814ca232f4d4","category":"Cycling"}